## DESIGN AND IMPLEMENTATION CONSTRAINTS

- Default view: latest 5 versions per source. "Show older versions" expands to all 20
- Badges: LATEST = gnNeonTeal, RECOMMENDED = gnAccentGlow, ACTIVE = gnAccentPrimary
- Download button: outlined gnAccentPrimary, shows Download icon + "Download" label + size
- Progress: circular indicator with percentage inside, full-width 2dp progress bar below row
- Use button: outlined gnBorderCard — makes it visually secondary to Download
- Remove button: gnStatusError text-only — destructive so low prominence
- Active version: checkmark only, no extra buttons — you can't remove the active version
- Release notes: tap row to expand/collapse, gnBgElevated background, bodySmall gnTextSecondary
- Cache-first: show Room data immediately, GitHub data merges in as it arrives
- Stagger GitHub requests 100ms apart per source to avoid rate limiting
- All downloads: cacheDir → extract → filesDir. Never external storage
- All Room reads/writes and network on Dispatchers.IO
- ACTIVE badge is per-game (scoped by appId) — two games can have different active versions
- After Turnip or Mesa install: call HardwareProfileCache.invalidate(context)
- No new colors — only existing gn_* tokens from Color.kt
- Fonts: GameNativeFontFamily (Outfit) via PluviaTypography everywhere
